The paper deals with coded caching schemes for communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel method for multicast message generation and delivery, which involves leveraging the network topology, and this could potentially fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents numerical evaluations of the proposed scheme, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
